comment._content: Possibly his younger brother, given NYT article of September 4, 1913, query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9400E5DA163DE633A... 'KING'S COUSIN HERE.; Sixty-one, Fancy Free, and Is "Open to Conviction." Among those who arrived from Liverpool yesterday on the Cunarder Carmania was Col. Sir Augustus Charles FitzGeorge, youngest son of the late Duke of Cambridge and second cousin to King George.' Wikipedia page for his father has him listed as: 12 June 1847- 30 October 1933 Col Sir Augustus FitzGeorge, KCVO, CB www.thepeerage.com/p10092.htm lists information on the three FitzGeorge brothers. Two of them had Augustus in their string of given names, but the Colonel had it as his first name.
